%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105775897%2Cimgsize-27182.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Ffinancial-frauds-on-the-rise-how-government-plans-to-check-sim-cloning-qr-code-digital-payments-fraud%2Farticleshow%2F105775407.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Indian%20government%20is%20looking%20to%20take%20measures%20to%20address%20the%20growing%20concern%20over%20digital%20financial%20frauds.%20Discussions%20have%20begun%20among%20key%20stakeholders%20to%20develop%20new%20filters%20and%20safeguards%20for%20digital%20transactions.%20Proposed%20measures%20include%20mandatory%20filters%20for%20high-value%20transactions%20and%20the%20use%20of%20one-time%20passwords.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20BUSINESS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Ffinancial-frauds-on-the-rise-how-government-plans-to-check-sim-cloning-qr-code-digital-payments-fraud%2Farticleshow%2F105775407.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22More%20Than%2010%2C000%20Daily%20Naps%3A%20How%20Chinstrap%20Penguins%20Adapt%20And%20Survive%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20us%20are%20accustomed%20to%20experiencing%20brief%20lapses%20into%20sleep%20while%20reading%20or%20working%20on%20a%20computer.%20Birds%2C%20too%2C%20are%20known%20to%20take%20in%20these%20microsleeps%2C%20but%20there%20is%20a%20particular%20species%20that%20seems%20to%20have%20honed%20the%20ability%20to%20master%20the%20art%20of%20short-lived%20slumbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20new%20study%2C%20breeding%20chinstrap%20penguins%20take%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20naps%20a%20day%2C%20with%20each%20nap%20lasting%20an%20average%20of%20four%20seconds.%20Employing%20this%20strategy%2C%20the%20animals%20amass%20approximately%2011%20hours%20of%20sleep%20daily%2C%20challenging%20the%20conventional%20human%20observation%20that%20sleep%20fragmentation%20is%20detrimental%20to%20sleep%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20that%20was%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.adh0771%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EScience%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20The%20authors%20studied%2014%20penguins%20nesting%20in%20a%20colony%20on%20King%20George%20Island%2C%20Antarctica.%20Over%2010%20days%20of%20observation%2C%20the%20birds%20never%20engaged%20in%20prolonged%20sleep.%20The%20longest%20nap%20registered%20was%2034%20seconds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20what%20was%20most%20striking%20and%20interesting-the%20fact%20that%20they%20can%20deal%20with%20sleeping%20in%20a%20fragmented%20way%20continuously%2C%20day%20and%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20co-author%20Paul-Antoine%20Libourel%2C%20a%20sleep%20ecophysiologist%20at%20the%20Neuroscience%20Research%20Center%20of%20Lyon%20in%20Bron%2C%20France.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fd41586-023-03751-7%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENature%20magazine%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20collect%20data%20on%20brain%20activity%2C%20the%20researchers%20implanted%20electrodes%20inside%20the%20penguins'%20skulls.%20This%20allowed%20the%20scientists%20to%20identify%20when%20the%20birds%20entered%20a%20state%20of%20slow-wave%20sleep%2C%20which%20is%20the%20dominant%20form%20of%20sleep%20in%20birds%20and%20also%20occurs%20in%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPenguins%20engaged%20in%20more%20than%20600%20short%20bouts%20of%20slow-wave%20sleep%20per%20hour.%20These%20bouts%20became%20even%20shorter%20and%20more%20frequent%20when%20the%20birds%20were%20caring%20for%20eggs%2C%20perhaps%20because%20they%20needed%20to%20be%20more%20alert%20while%20incubating%2C%20the%20researchers%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701846180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fjid8kppg_chinstrap-penguins-_625x300_06_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%2