3A%22%3Cp%3EBusiness%20magazine%20Forbes%20has%20released%20its%20annual%20list%20of%20the%20World's%20Most%20Powerful%20Women%20for%202023%2C%20and%20it%20features%20four%20Indians.%20These%20women%20have%20not%20only%20shattered%20glass%20ceilings%20but%20also%20etched%20their%20names%20on%20the%20global%20stage%2C%20showcasing%20the%20diverse%20and%20influential%20voices%20emerging%20from%20India.%20To%20determine%20the%20rank%2C%20Forbes%20had%20four%20metrics%3A%20money%2C%20media%2C%20impact%20and%20spheres%20of%20influence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20world%20celebrates%20their%20achievements%2C%20these%20four%20Indian%20women%20stand%20as%20powerful%20symbols%20of%20resilience%2C%20leadership%2C%20and%20excellence%20in%20the%20global%20arena%3A%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3ENirmala%20Sitharaman%20(ranked%2032)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F4-indians-in-forbes-most-powerful-women-list-nirmala-sitharaman-at-32-4637687%5C%22%3ENirmala%20Sitharaman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2064%2C%20is%20a%20senior%20figure%20in%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20and%20has%20been%20India's%20Minister%20of%20Finance%20and%20Minister%20of%20Corporate%20Affairs%20since%202019.%20Ms%20Sitharaman%20served%20as%20the%2028th%20Defence%20Minister%20from%202017%20to%202019%2C%20making%20her%20India's%20second%20female%20defence%20minister%20and%20finance%20minister%20after%20Indira%20Gandhi.%20In%202022%2C%20Forbes%20ranked%20her%2036th%20in%20the%202022%20list%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20powerful%20women%20and%20this%20year%20she%20was%20ranked%2032nd.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3ERoshni%20Nadar%20Malhotra%20(ranked%2060)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnRoshni%20Nadar%20Malhotra%2C%2042%2C%20is%20an%20Indian%20billionaire%20and%20philanthropist.%20She%20is%20the%20chairperson%20of%20HCL%20Technologies%2C%20making%20history%20as%20the%20first%20woman%20to%20lead%20a%20listed%20IT%20company%20in%20India.%20As%20the%20only%20child%20of%20HCL%20founder%20Shiv%20Nadar%2C%20she%20is%20recognised%20as%20the%20richest%20woman%20in%20India%2C%20according%20to%20the%20IIFL%20Wealth%20Hurun%20India%20Rich%20List%20(2019).%20Ms%20Malhotra%20has%20consistently%20been%20ranked%20among%20the%20world's%20most%20powerful%20women%20by%20Forbes%2C%20holding%20the%2054th%20position%20in%202019%2C%2055th%20in%202020%20and%2060th%20in%202023.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3ESoma%20Mondal%20(ranked%2070)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnSoma%20Mondal%2C%2060%2C%20is%20the%20current%20Chairperson%20of%20the%20Steel%20Authority%20of%20India%2C%20making%20history%20as%20the%20first%20woman%20in%20this%20role%20since%20January%202021.%20Born%20in%20Bhubaneswar%2C%20she%20graduated%20in%20Electrical%20Engineering%20in%201984.%20With%20over%2035%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20metal%20industry%2C%20she%20started%20at%20NALCO%20and%20rose%20to%20become%20Director%20(Commercial)%20before%20joining%20SAIL%20in%202017.%20Ms%20Mondal's%20career%20milestones%20include%20being%20the%20first%20woman%20Functional%20Director%20and%20Chairman%20at%20SAIL.%20Beyond%20her%20corporate%20achievements%2C%20she%20holds%20the%20position%20of%20Chairperson%20of%20SCOPE%20and%20was%20honoured%20as%20'CEO%20of%20the%20Year'%20at%20the%20ETPrime%20Women%20Leadership%20Awards%20in%202023.%20She%20ranks%2070th%20on%20the%20list.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EKiran%20Mazumdar-Shaw%20(ranked%2076)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnKiran%20Mazumdar-Shaw%2C%2070%2C%20is%20a%20prominent%20Indian%20billionaire%20entrepreneur.%20She%20founded%20and%20led%20Biocon%20Limited%20and%20Biocon%20Biologics%20Limited%20in%20Bangalore%2C%20India.%20Besides%20her%20role%20in%20the%20biotechnology%20companies%2C%20she%20was%20the%20former%20chairperson%20of%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Management%2C%20Bangalore.%20Ms%20Mazumdar-Shaw%20has%20received%20numerous%20accolades%2C%20including%20the%20Othme