the%20visit%20of%20a%20senior%20White%20House%20official%20to%20New%20Delhi%20this%20week%2C%20but%20there%20was%20silence%20from%20the%20Indian%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20principal%20deputy%20national%20security%20advisor%20Jon%20Finer%C2%A0led%20delegation-level%20talks%20for%20a%20review%20of%20the%20US-India%20Initiative%20on%20Critical%20and%20Emerging%20Technology%20(iCET)%2C%20co-chaired%20with%20his%20Indian%20counterpart%2C%20Vikram%20Misri.%20He%20also%20participated%20in%20the%20global%20technology%20summit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37333%2FVisit%2Bof%2BUS%2BPrincipal%2BDeputy%2BNational%2BSecurity%2BAdviser%2Bto%2BIndia%2BDecember%2B04%2B2023%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20press%20release%20issued%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0on%20Monday%20talked%20about%20the%20iCET%20agenda%20in%20relative%20detail.%20It%20also%20mentioned%20that%20%E2%80%9Ckey%20bilateral%20issues%E2%80%9D%20were%20discussed%2C%20but%20did%20not%20cite%20them%20specifically.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20White%20House%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2023%2F12%2F04%2Freadout-of-principal-deputy-national-security-advisor-jon-finers-travel-to-india%2F%5C%22%3Ereadout%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20Finer%E2%80%99s%20visit%20was%20more%20explicit.%20%E2%80%9CMr.%20Finer%20acknowledged%20India%E2%80%99s%20establishment%20of%20a%20Committee%20of%20Enquiry%20to%20investigate%20lethal%20plotting%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20importance%20of%20holding%20accountable%20anyone%20found%20responsible%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20at%20the%20Global%20Technology%20Summit%20in%20Delhi%2C%20organised%20by%20the%20MEA%20and%20Carnegie%20India%2C%20Finer%20highlighted%20the%20enduring%20challenges%20in%20the%20India-US%20relationship%20up%20to%20the%20present%20day.%20He%20acknowledged%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccomplicated%20history%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20relationship%20and%20emphasised%20that%2C%20across%20various%20administrations%20in%20both%20countries%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20demonstrated%20ability%20to%20navigate%20difficulties.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20many%20difficult%20issues%20that%20remain%20in%20relationship%2C%20right%20up%20to%20the%20present%20day%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20that%20both%20sides%20demonstrated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20can%20work%20through%20our%20differences%20in%20a%20constructive%20way%20without%20derailing%20the%20broader%20cooperative%20agenda.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20has%20been%20no%20official%20response%20from%20the%20Indian%20side%20to%20the%20White%20House%E2%80%99s%20statement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fpannun-assassination-plot-india-enquiry-committee-set-up%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%2029%2C%20US%20federal%20prosecutors%20filed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20fresh%20new%20charges%20against%20an%20Indian%20citizen%2C%20Nikhil%20Gupta%2C%20for%20being%20involved%20in%20a%20plot%20to%20kill%20a%20Sikh-American%20member%20of%20a%20Khalistani%20group%20which%20is%20banned%20by%20New%20Delhi.%20The%20charges%20also%20accuse%20an%20unnamed%20but%20%E2%80%9Cidentified%20Indian%20government%20employee%E2%80%9D%20of%20directing%20the%20failed%20plot.%20The%20indictment%20also%20appears%20to%20link%20the%20Indian%20official%20with%20the%20killing%20of%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20a%20Canadian%20Khalistani%20activist%2C%20in%20June.%20A%20US%20undercover%20law%20enforcement%20personnel%20was%20allegedly%20recruited%20to%20be%20the%20hitman.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20charges%20did%20not%20name%20the%20Sikh-American%20citizen%2C%20he%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%2C%20general%20counsel%20of%20the%20proscribed%20group%2C%20%E2%80%98Sikhs%20for%20Justice%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20indictment%2C%20India%20had%20said%20that%20it%20was%20looking%20into%20the%20complaint%20and%20had%20set%20up%20an%20inquiry%20committee%20to%20investigate%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20US%20media%20reports%2C%20senior%20US%20administration%20officials%2C%20including%20NSA%20Jake%20Sullivan%20and%20CIA%20chief%20William%20Burns%2C%20had%20already%20raised%20the%20matter%20with%20the%20Indian%20government%20since%20August.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFiner%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20India%20is%20the%20first%20by%20a%20senior%20US%20administration%20official%20following%20the%20charges%20being%20made%20public.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20held%20talks%20with%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Ajit%20Doval%2C%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20and%20foreign%20secretary%20Vinay%20Kwatra.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fbriefings%2Fdepartment-press-briefing-december-4-2023%2F%23post-507198-INDIALAWENFORCEMENT%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20State%20Department%20on%20Monday%20also%20underlined%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20Washington%20was%20looking%20forward%20to%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20committee%20set%20up%20by%20the%20Indian%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20I%20would%20say%20that%20when%20these%20%E2%80%93%20when%20this%20alleged%20incident%20was%20brought%20to%20our%20attention%2C%20we%20made%20very%20clear%20at%20the%20most%20senior%20levels%20of%20our%20government%20to%20the%20most%20senior%20levels%20of%20the%20Indian%20Government%20how%20seriously%20we%20would%20treat%20something%20like%20this.%20They%20have%20opened%20an%20investigation%20into%20the%20matter%20and%20we%20look%20forward%20to%20seeing%20the%20results%20of%20that%20investigation%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20state%20department%20spokesperson%20Matthew%20Miller.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20the%20question%20about%20media%20reports%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20intelligence%20services%20conducting%20similar%20operations%20in%20neighbouring%20countries%2C%20Miller%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20made%20clear%20that%20we%20oppose%20transnational%20oppression%20no%20matter%20where%20it%20occurs%20or%20who%20might%20be%20conducting%20it.%20That%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20comment%20specific%20to%20India.%20That%E2%80%99s%20a%20comment%20specific%20to%20any%20country%20in%20the%20world.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701786887000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F05195920%2F393119085_17950677671711587_3454257721892670160_n.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffirst-visit-pannun-plot-us-accountability-india-silent-publicly%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Principal%20deputy%20national%20security%20advisor%20Jon%20Finer%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20India%20is%20the%20first%20by%20a%20senior%20US%20administration%20official%20following%20the%20charges%20being%20made%20public.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Ffirst-visit-pannun-plot-us-accountability-india-silent-publicly%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shane%20MacGowan%20'pushed%20the%20boundaries%20of%20what%20humans%20can%20do%20to%20their%20bodies'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701784740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F768x432%2Fskynews-shane-macgowan-singer_6361217.jpg%3F20231115102913%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fshane-macgowan-pushed-the-boundaries-of-what-humans-can-do-to-their-bodies-says-wife-13023435%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shane%20MacGowan's%20widow%20said%20sh