rk%20of%20resistance.%20What%E2%80%99s%20more%2C%20after%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20October%20strike%2C%20Israel%20imprisoned%20around%20200%20West%20Bank%20residents%2C%20apprehending%20them%20from%20the%20streets%2C%20and%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20even%20from%20their%20homes.%20News%20reports%20say%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F12%2F3%2Fhow-a-palestinian-teens-release-exposed-israeli-mistreatment-of-prisoners%5C%22%3Echarges%3C%2Fa%3E%20brought%20against%20them%20may%20be%20fabricated.%20This%20appears%20little%20different%20from%20the%20abduction%20of%20Israeli%20citizens%20by%20Hamas%20fighters%20on%20October%207%20which%20was%20widely%20seen%20as%20an%20act%20of%20%E2%80%9Cterrorism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22162028%2Fgaza-israel-barrier.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22162028%2Fgaza-israel-barrier.jpg%201000w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22162028%2Fgaza-israel-barrier-300x184.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685931%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22614%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20barrier%20between%20Israel%20and%20Gaza.%20Photo%3A%20%C2%A0IDF%20Spokesperson%E2%80%99s%20Unit%2C%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHamas%20is%20a%20Palestinian%20entity%20from%20Gaza%2C%20but%20its%20stock%20appears%20to%20have%20soared%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20following%20the%20release%20of%20West%20Bank%20prisoners.%20On%20the%20first%20day%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fgallery%2F2023%2F12%2F1%2Fphotos-palestinians-celebrate-release-of-another-batch-of-prisoners%5C%22%3Eprisoner%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ordinary%20people%20on%20West%20Bank%20streets%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fpalestinians-israel-prisoner-exchange-hostage-92545883b1fef86fb9b34549b7deca58%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edraped%20themselves%20in%20Hamas%20flags%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20Fatah%20faction%20of%20what%E2%80%99s%20now%20the%20disintegrated%20Palestinian%20Liberation%20Organisation%20(PLO)%2C%20led%20by%20the%20once%20redoubtable%20Yasser%20Arafat%2C%20enjoys%20only%20nominal%20authority%20now%2C%20and%20evidently%20little%20public%20esteem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETechnically%2C%20it%20still%20runs%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20(PA).%20But%20the%20question%20is%3A%20Where%20is%20the%20PA%20when%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Jerusalem%20are%20under%20Israeli%20jackboots%3F%20The%20PA%20appeared%20to%20be%20pretty%20much%20somnolent%20after%20the%20watershed%20incident%20of%20October%207%2C%20although%20to%20their%20credit%2C%20the%20PA%20ambassadors%20in%20London%20and%20New%20Delhi%20forcefully%20conveyed%20the%20anguish%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20and%20the%20colonial%20brutality%20of%20Israel%20even%20when%20the%20media%20set%20out%20to%20seek%20from%20them%20a%20condemnation%20of%20Hamas%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%E2%80%9D%20outfit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-hamas-karan-thapar-paola-caridi-interview%5C%22%3EWatch%20%7C%20Everything%20You%20Need%20to%20Know%20About%20Hamas%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Celimination%E2%80%9D%20of%20Hamas%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20brief%20pause%20and%20the%20resulting%20hostages%20and%20prisoners%20exchange%2C%20was%20not%20going%20to%20lead%20to%20a%20comprehensive%20ceasefire%20and%20the%20cessation%20of%20hostilities%20by%20the%20Netanhayu%20government%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20peace%20formulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20the%20Israeli%20government%E2%80%99s%20goal%20is%20clearly%20ill-conceived%20as%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20accomplish.%20Powerful%20ideas%2C%20such%20as%20the%20fight%20against%20colonial%20oppression%20and%20foreign%20occupation%2C%20live%20through%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20relentless%20bombardment%20of%20Gaza%2C%20including%20its%20most%20important%20hospitals%2C%20the%20Israeli%20state%20is%20now%20being%20questioned%20on%20moral%20grounds.%20People%20around%20the%20world%20have%20refused%20to%20accept%20false%20Israeli%20propaganda%20%E2%80%93%20that%20Hamas%20was%20using%20the%20famous%20al-Shifa%20hospital%20as%20a%20military%20command%20and%20control%20centre%20%E2%80%93%20as%20a%20justification%20for%20its%20targeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetanyahu%20has%20to%20be%20a%20%3Cem%3Eschmuck%3C%2Fem%3E%20not%20to%20see%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeading%20governments%20of%20the%20South%2C%20such%20as%20Brazil%20and%20South%20Africa%2C%20and%20several%20others%2C%20have%20downgraded%20or%20even%20cut%20off%20diplomatic%20ties%20with%20Israel.%20However%2C%20India%2C%20under%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20is%20an%20exception%20among%20non-Western%20powers.%20It%20has%20demonstrated%20unquestioning%20support%20for%20the%20Netanyahu%20regime%20and%20its%20relentless%20military%20assault%20on%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20influential%20Western%20circles%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20US%2C%20it%20is%20being%20posited%20that%20Israel%20has%20placed%20itself%20on%20the%20same%20plane%20as%20Hamas%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20decried%20as%20%E2%80%9Cterrorist%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20by%20bombarding%20the%20unarmed%20civilian%20population%20of%20Gaza.%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%2C%20standing%20four-square%20behind%20the%20Israeli%20action%2C%20has%20not%20only%20discredited%20himself%20but%2C%20quite%20possibly%2C%20ensured%20the%20loss%20of%20support%20in%20the%20large%20constituency%20of%20the%20young%20in%20the%202024%20presidential%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArab%20governments%20that%20were%20until%20recently%20moving%20toward%20an%20economic%20and%20political%20rapprochement%20with%20Israel%20under%20US%20inducement%20and%20facilitation%2C%20leaving%20the%20Palestine%20question%20hanging%20fire%2C%20are%20showing%20signs%20of%20holding%20back.%20They%20are%20only%20too%20keenly%20aware%20of%20the%20strong%20anti-Israel%20and%20anti-US%20sentiment%20sweeping%20through%20public%20opinion%20in%20their%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20Palestinian%20side%2C%20it%20is%20Hamas%20which%20is%20now%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20things%2C%20not%20Fatah%20or%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20of%20President%20Abbas%2C%20in%20spite%20of%20the%20recent%20best%20efforts%20of%20Israel%20and%20the%20US%20to%20bring%20the%20PA%20into%20play.%20While%20Hamas%20appears%20to%20have%20emerged%20as%20the%20new%20hope%20of%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20the%20political%20star%20of%20Netanyahu%20can%20fairly%20be%20said%20to%20be%20in%20decline.%20There%20is%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20weighty%20speculation%20in%20Israel%20that%20the%20prime%20minister%20can%20hold%20his%20position%20only%20so%20long%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cwar%E2%80%9D%20(a%20strange%20language%20for%20a%20one-sided%20attack%20on%20millions%20of%20civilians)%20lasts%2C%20as%20it%20is%20impolitic%20to%20dump%20the%20national%20leader%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20military%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fresisting-the-zionist-revisionism-of-gandhi%5C%22%3EResisting%20the%20Zionist%20Revisionism%20of%20Gandhi%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM-300x185.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x632.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685141%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22741%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Sheikh%20Redwan%20neighbourhood%20of%20Gaza%20city%2C%20October%208%2C%202023.%20Photo%3A%20Bashar%20Taleb%2FUN%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20high%20stakes%20game%20for%20Israel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20much-touted%20mission%20of%20eliminating%20Hamas%20is%20incapable%20of%20being%20realised.%20Even%20if%20the%20Gaza-based%20Hamas%20leaders%20are%20all%20killed%2C%20new%20ones%20will%20emerge%20elsewhere.%20The%20killing%20or%20destruction%20of%20an%20idea%20can%20only%20be%20called%20a%20fool%E2%80%99s%20errand.%20In%20reality%2C%20if%20not%20today%2C%20then%20some%20other%20day%2C%20it%20is%20Hamas%20with%20which%20those%20interested%20in%20eventually%20negotiating%20the%20complex%20Palestinian%20question%20will%20have%20to%20deal.%20This%20includes%20Israel%2C%20the%20US%2C%20and%20the%20prominent%20Arab%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20Netanyahu%20or%20no%20Netanyahu%2C%20Biden%20or%20no%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20so-called%20objective%20of%20eliminating%20Hamas%20is%20a%20red%20herring.%20The%20real%2C%20hidden%20aim%20behind%20keeping%20up%20the%20military%20attack%20appears%20to%20be%20to%20drive%20out%20the%20Palestinians%20from%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20%E2%80%93%20giving%20effect%20to%20a%20second%20%3Cem%3Enaqba%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20first%20%3Cem%3Enaqba%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20in%201948%20when%20Palestinians%20were%20driven%20out%20of%20their%20land%20upon%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Israel.%20And%20now%20they%20are%20to%20be%20driven%20out%20of%20the%20lands%20to%20which%20they%20were%20forced%20to%20flee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20mocks%20history%20when%20the%20Israel%20leadership%2C%20and%20echoing%20with%20them%20the%20North%20Americans%20and%20the%20West%20Europeans%20and%20their%20current%20allies%2C%20the%20Indians%2C%20says%20it%20has%20the%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20defend%20itself%E2%80%9D.%20The%20question%20is%20from%20whom%3F%20From%20the%20people%20whose%20land%20it%20has%20occupied%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fanand-k-sahay%5C%22%3EAnand%20K.%20Sahay%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20political%20commentator%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701783918000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F01111519%2Fimage1170x530cropped.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisraels-hamas-red-herring-evicting-palestinians-gaza%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tel%20Aviv%20knows%20that%20even%20if%20the%20Gaza-based%20Hamas%20leaders%20are%20all%20killed%2C%20new%20ones%20will%20emerge%20elsewhere%2C%20and%20that%20it%20is%20impossible%20to%20kill%20or%20destroy%20the%20idea%20of%20freedom.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisraels-hamas-red-herring-evicting-palestinians-gaza%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22France%20votes%20to%20ban%20disposable%20vapes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701782700000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-vaping-smoking-e-cigarette_6382918.jpg%3F20231205133924%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ffrance-votes-to-ban-disposable-vapes-13023409%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20bill%20to%20ban%20the%20single%20use%20of%20disposable%20e-cigarettes%20has%20been%20approved%20in%20France.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A150%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ffrance-votes-to-ban-disposable-vapes-13023409%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Ffrance-votes-to-ban-disposable-vapes-13023409%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Ffrance-votes-to-ban-disposable-vapes-13023409%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Revanth%20Reddy%20Will%20Be%20Telangana%20Chief%20Minister%2C%20Confirms%20Rahul%20Gandhi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F05182152%2Frahul-revanth.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20face%20of%20the%20Congress%20campaign%20in%20Telangana%2C%20Anumula%20Revanth%20Reddy%2C%20has%20been%20chosen%20as%20the%20new%20chief%20minister%20of%20the%20southern%20state%2C%20senior%20Congress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20said%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20December%205.%20He%20will%20be%20sworn%20in%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20decision%20was%20taken%20at%20a%20meeting%20attended%20by%20Congress%20president%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20and%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20general%20secretary%20(organisation)%20K.C.%20Venugopal%2C%20apart%20from%20leaders%20like%20D.K.%20Shivakumar%2C%20who%20apparently%20conveyed%20to%20the%20central%20leadership%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20newly-elected%20legislators%20in%20the%20state%20preferred%20Revanth%20Reddy%20over%20others.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftelangana-news%2Fcongress-revanth-reddy-to-be-telangana-chief-minister-sources-4635221%23pfrom%3Dhome-ndtv_bigstory%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENDTV%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reported%20that%2042%20of%20the%2064%20Congress%20MLAs%20supported%20Revanth%20Reddy.%20Earlier%2C%20the%20Congress%20had%20decided%20to%20conduct%20the%20swearing-in%20ceremony%20on%20December%206%2C%20which%20was%20postponed%20following%20%E2%80%9Cobjections%E2%80%9D%20to%20Revanth%E2%80%99s%20candidature.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReports%20said%20that%20leaders%20like%20former%20Congress%20legislature%20party%20(CLP)%20leader%20Bhatti%20Vikramarka%2C%20former%20Congress%20state%20chief%20N.%20Uttam%20Kumar%20Reddy%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eformer%20minister%20Komatireddy%20Venkat%20Reddy%20and%20former%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20Damodar%20Raja%20Narasimha%20were%20among%20those%20who%20opposed%20Revanth%20Reddy%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20he%20had%20corruption%20cases%20against%20him%20and%20could%20not%20deliver%20a%20majority%20of%20assembly%20seats%20in%20his%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency%20Malkajgiri.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20of%20these%20leaders%20had%20also%20opposed%20Revanth%E2%80%99s%20leadership%20and%20called%20him%20a%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%20(TDP)%20implant%20in%20the%20Congress.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERevanth%20Reddy%20had%20joined%20the%20Congress%20from%20the%20TDP%20and%20was%20considered%20close%20to%20N.%20Chandrababu%20Naidu.%20He%20had%20begun%20his%20political%20career%20as%20an%20Akhil%20Bharatiya%20Vidyarthi%20Parishad%20leader%2C%20traversing%20through%20many%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Fwho-is-revanth-reddy-the-man-who-has-dethroned-kcr-in-telangana%5C%22%3Eincluding%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Telangana%20(now%20Bharat)%20Rashtra%20Samithi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20was%20made%20the%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20state%20unit%20chief%20in%202021%2C%20soon%20after%20joining.%20In%20his%20role%20as%20the%20Pradesh%20Congress%20Committee%20president%2C%20he%20organised%20multiple%20rallies%20in%20which%20he%20aggressively%20attacked%20chief%20minister%20K.%20Chandrashekar%20Rao%20(KCR)%20and%20his%20government%20for%20failing%20to%20meet%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20expectations.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20strategy%20worked%20in%20reviving%20the%20Congress%20and%20dislodged%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20was%20fast%20emerging%20as%20the%20primary%20opposition%20party%20in%20the%20state.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20central%20leadership%E2%80%99s%20decision%20swayed%20towards%20Revanth%20Reddy%20as%20his%20energetic%20leadership%20is%20credited%20with%20reviving%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20fortunes%20in%20Telangana%2C%20where%20it%20was%20down%20and%20out%20after%20a%20majority%20of%20its%20MLAs%20in%20the%20last%20assembly%20merged%20with%20the%20BRS.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReddy%20does%20not%20come%20from%20a%20political%20family%2C%20as%20is%20usually%20the%20norm%20among%20top-rung%20leaders%20in%20the%20Telugu%20states.%20He%20is%2C%20however%2C%20married%20to%20Geetha%2C%20the%20niece%20of%20late%20Congress%20leader%20and%20former%20Union%20minister%20S.%20Jaipal%20Reddy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3ERevanth%20Reddy%20has%20often%20rubbed%20KCR%20the%20wrong%20way.%20Though%20they%20never%20confronted%20each%20other%20after%20Revanth%20Reddy%20lost%20in%20the%202018%20assembly%20elections%2C%20the%20Congress%20leader%20took%20aggressive%20jibes%20at%20KCR%20in%20public%20speeches%20whenever%20he%20got%20the%20chance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20bad%20blood%20between%20the%20two%20grew%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20Revanth%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20arrest%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98sting%20operation%E2%80%99%20carried%20out%20to%20trap%20him%20while%20offering%20a%20bribe%20of%20Rs%2050%20lakh%20to%20a%20legislator%20of%20the%20then-Telangana%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20in%20the%20elections%20to%20Telangana%E2%80%99s%20legislative%20council.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3ERevanth%20Reddy%20continues%20to%20nurse%20a%20grouse%20against%20KCR%20that%20he%20came%20out%20of%20jail%20in%20the%20case%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fnaidu-ministers-attend-revanth-daughters-2132696%5C%22%3Eon%20a%20twelve-hour%20bail%3C%2Fa%3E%20granted%20by%20the%20courts%20to%20perform%20the%20marriage%20of%20his%20only%20daughter%2C%20Nymisha%20Reddy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20case%20appeared%20to%20be%20a%20Damocles%E2%80%99s%20sword%20hung%20above%20his%20head%20by%20KCR%2C%20but%20Reddy%20has%20nevertheless%20managed%20to%20climb%20to%20the%20top.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EReddy%20went%20to%20jail%20for%20a%20few%20days%20on%20another%20occasion%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftelangana%2Frevanth-reddy-arrested-illegal-drone-use-farmhouse-allegedly-owned-ktr-119606%5C%22%3Eallegedly%20shooting%20a%20video%20with%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20farmhouse%20of%20KCR%E2%80%99s%20son%20and%20minister%20K.T.%20Rama%20Rao%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20verbal%20abuse%20between%20the%20father-son%20duo%20one%20the%20one%20hand%20and%20Revanth%20Reddy%20on%20the%20other%20touched%20a%20crescendo%20in%20the%20campaign%20for%20the%20recently%20concluded%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBhatti%20Vikramarka%20and%20N.%20Uttam%20Kumar%20Reddy%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20also%20played%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20victory%2C%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20made%20deputy%20chief%20ministers.%20Vikramarka%20led%20a%201500-km-long%20foot%20rally%20in%20the%20state%2C%20while%20Uttam%20Reddy%20consolidated%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20ranks%20and%20helped%20the%20party%20mount%20an%20effective%20campaign%20against%20the%20popular%20KCR.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWith%20inputs%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fn-rahul%2F%5C%22%3EN.%20Rahul%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701781185000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F05182152%2Frahul-revanth.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Frevanth-reddy-telangana-chief-minister-rahul-gandhi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20reports%2C%2042%20of%20the%2064%20Congress%20MLAs%20supported%20Revanth%20Reddy%20despite%20some%20influential%20leaders%20opposing%20his%20candidature.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Frevanth-reddy-telangana-chief-minister-rahul-gandhi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20these%20few%20tiny%20words%20fuel%20major%20disputes%20at%20climate%20negotiations%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701780420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-cop28-fossil-fuels_6383496.jpg%3F20231205211321%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fthe-worlds-energy-future-is-being-decided-at-cop28-these-few-words-could-decide-how-it-unfolds-13023381%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Right%20now%20in%20Dubai%2C%20pretty%20much%20every%20government%20in%20the%20world%20is%20debating%20what%20kind%20of%20energy%20we%20will%20all%20be%20using%20in%20just%2025%20years'%20time%2C%20which%20will%20influence%20the%20climate%20we%20live%20in%20and%20the%20air%20we%20breathe.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A55%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fthe-worlds-energy-future-is-being-decided-at-cop28-these-few-words-could-decide-how-it-unfolds-13023381%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fthe-worlds-energy-future-is-being-decided-at-cop28-these-few-words-could-decide-how-it-unfolds-13023381%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fthe-worlds-energy-future-is-being-decided-at-cop28-these-few-words-could-decide-how-it-unfolds-13023381%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20the%20War%20in%20Palestine%20Is%20Being%20Broadcast%20Amid%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Growing%20Attacks%20on%20Journalists%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19092706%2FF8t8SUEWMAAvoa0.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20a%20limited%20ceasefire%20with%20Hamas%20was%20being%20finalised%20on%20November%2022%2C%20with%20a%20deal%20to%20release%2050%20hostages%20over%20a%20period%20of%20four%20days%2C%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20reiterated%20that%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%20will%20not%20stop%20with%20this.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20continue%20the%20war%20until%20Gaza%20will%20not%20threaten%20Israel%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20What%20this%20means%20is%20that%20Gaza%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20an%20intensely%20life%20threatening%20workplace%20for%20journalists.%20Over%20the%20last%20few%20weeks%20Gaza%20has%20turned%20into%20a%20war%20front%20where%20journalists%20themselves%20have%20become%20victimised%20news-subjects%20as%20well%20as%20a%20moving%20picture%20of%20bravery%20and%20human%20resilience.%20And%2C%20in%20the%20process%2C%20a%20new%20and%20unique%20journalism%20phenomenon%20has%20also%20emerged%20from%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20the%20world%20only%20noticed%20the%20regular%20reporting%20of%20big%20media%20organisations%20like%20Al%20Jazeera%20from%20Gaza.%20Reporters%20from%20other%20international%20media%20were%20by%20and%20large%20unable%20to%20enter%20Gaza.%20It%20was%20amidst%20this%20that%20this%20new%20media%20phenomenon%20emerged.%20This%20was%20essentially%20linked%20to%20the%20new%20age%20of%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20phenomenon%20was%20the%20almost%20overnight%20transformation%20of%20Gazan%20content%20creators%E2%80%94those%20who%20celebrated%20their%20lives%20as%20social%20media%20stars%20capturing%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20culture%2C%20food%2C%20and%20sights%E2%80%94into%20war%20reporters.%20They%20were%20not%20even%20familiar%20with%20the%20rough%20life%20of%20a%20normal%20peacetime%20reporter.%20Still%2C%20standing%20on%20the%20thin%20line%20between%20life%20and%20death%2C%20staring%20at%20near-certain%20death%20that%20would%20follow%20if%20one%20misstep%20happened%2C%20they%20began%20to%20speak%20to%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20%E2%80%9Cnew%E2%80%9D%20journalists%20as%20well%20as%20existing%20professional%20journalists%20became%20victims%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza.%20We%20cannot%20see%20them%20separately.%20Both%20conventional%20journalists%20as%20well%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20ones%E2%80%9D%20showed%20and%20continue%20to%20show%20extraordinary%20courage%2C%20commitment%20and%20endurance%20in%20the%20face%20of%20unprecedented%20human%20tragedies.%20Some%20of%20them%20may%20have%20biases.%20But%20their%20significance%20and%20courage%20cannot%20be%20underestimated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20writing%20this%2C%20reports%20say%2053%20of%20the%20journalists%20and%20media%20workers%20reporting%20from%20Gaza%20and%20Israel%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20the%20war.%20The%20Committee%20to%20Protect%20Journalists%20(CPJ)%2C%20a%20New%20York-based%20NGO%2C%20says%2046%20Palestinian%20journalists%2C%204%20Israeli%20journalists%20and%203%20Lebanese%20journalists%20were%20killed.%20The%20group%20said%20four%20Israeli%20journalists%20were%20killed%20in%20a%20Hamas%20attack%20on%20October%207%2C%20and%203%20Lebanese%20journalists%20were%20killed%20on%20the%20Israel-Lebanon%20border.%20Apart%20from%20this%2C%203%20journalists%20are%20missing%2C%2011%20journalists%20injured%20and%2018%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fpalestine-gaza-israel-journalist-media%5C%22%3EMore%20Than%20One%20Journalist%20Per%20Day%20Is%20Dying%20in%20the%20Israel-Gaza%20Conflict.%20This%20Has%20to%20Stop%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20the%20social%20media%20content%20creators-turned%20war%20reporters%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20world%20would%20never%20have%20understood%20the%20horrors%20of%20this%20war.%20It%20is%20indeed%20a%20breathtaking%20experience%20as%20you%20see%20these%20content%20creators%20jumping%20into%20the%20flames%20of%20war%20in%20the%20historical%20social%20and%20geographical%20background%20of%20the%20wondrously%20beautiful%20locales%20of%20Middle%20East%20Asia.%20The%20region%20has%20often%20been%20described%20as%20the%20cradle%20of%20human%20civilisation.%20This%20combined%20with%20the%20rich%20hues%20of%20the%20unique%20culture%20of%20the%20persecuted%20and%20hunted%20people%20called%20Palestinians%20make%20this%20media%20experience%20truly%20heroic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20brave%20media%20warriors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20look%20a%20little%20closely%20at%20some%20of%20these%20brave%20media%20warriors.%20For%20instance%2C%20there%20is%2025-year-old%20Bizan%20Awda%2C%20who%20viewers%20used%20to%20see%20as%20a%20smiling%20girl%20at%20a%20women%E2%80%99s%20boxing%20training%20facility%20in%20Gaza%2C%20wearing%20boxing%20gloves%20on%20her%20hands%2C%20and%20stating%20that%20the%20sport%20is%20unfamiliar%20to%20Gazan%20women%2C%20but%20they%20must%20come%20and%20try%20it.%20This%20%E2%80%9Cboxing%20coach%20video%E2%80%9D%20is%20an%20old%20story%20now.%20Bizan%20is%20now%20known%20as%20the%20journalist%20who%20broke%20down%20into%20tears%20while%20reporting%20that%20she%20was%20at%20the%20entrance%20of%20a%20hospital%20in%20Gaza%20just%20two%20seconds%20before%20a%20bomb%20fell%20and%20many%20people%20died.%20In%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Bizan%20could%20be%20seen%20jovially%20interacting%20with%20the%20small%20children%20who%20were%20cleaning%20the%20premises%20of%20Al%20Shifa%20Hospital%2C%20helping%20others%20however%20they%20could%2C%20trying%20to%20make%20them%20laugh.%20The%20laughter%20has%20stopped%20now.%20The%20girl%E2%80%99s%20face%20now%20is%20permanently%20shadowed%20by%20fear%20and%20excruciating%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahmoud%20Suwaitar%20is%20a%20comedian%20from%20Gaza.%20One%20of%20the%20founders%20of%20Tashweesh%2C%20a%20comedy%20troupe%20in%20Gaza.%20Before%20the%20war%2C%20he%20had%20600%2C000%20Instagram%20followers.%20Now%20Mahmood%20Suwaitar%20is%20reporting%20the%20war.%20With%20980%2C000%20followers%20on%20Instagram%2C%20Ahmed%20Hijazi%20had%20become%20a%20social%20media%20star%20capturing%20the%20culture%20and%20beauty%20of%20Gaza.%20Al%20Jazeera%20reported%20that%20Hijazi%E2%80%99s%20wife%20had%20a%20photo%20studio%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Tower%2C%20which%20was%20bombed%20by%20Israel%20in%20the%20early%20days%20of%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPlastia%20Alaqat%20is%20another%2020-year-old%20Gazan%20vlogger.%20Plastia%20used%20to%20make%20videos%20that%20focused%20on%20women%E2%80%99s%20education.%20Since%20the%20war%20began%2C%20this%20vlogger%20has%20given%20an%20incredibly%20honest%20account%20of%20how%20the%20war%20affects%20her%20on%20an%20everyday%20basis.%20Ali%20Nisman%20was%20a%20Palestinian%20actor%2C%20social%20activist%20and%20content%20creator%20killed%20in%20an%20Israeli%20bombing%20on%20October%2013.%20Even%20a%20few%20hours%20before%20that%2C%20Nisman%20had%20uploaded%20a%20video%20on%20his%20Instagram%20page%20reporting%20on%20the%20suffering%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Gaza.%20Nisman%E2%80%99s%20roles%20in%20the%202022%20film%20%E2%80%98Nasr%20Gilboa%20Street%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20television%20series%20%E2%80%98Sky%20Gate%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Al%20Rooh%E2%80%99%20had%20won%20great%20acclaim%20from%20the%20film%20buffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM-300x185.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F17091305%2FScreenshot-2023-11-17-at-9.12.38%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x632.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685141%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22741%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Sheikh%20Redwan%20neighbourhood%20of%20Gaza%20city%2C%20October%208%2C%202023.%3Cbr%3EPhoto%3A%20Bashar%20Taleb%2FUN%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world%20saw%20Al%20Jazeera%E2%80%99s%20reporter%20Yumna%20El%20Sayed%20reporting%20live%20the%20Israeli%20bombardment%20of%20a%20Gaza%20Tower%20just%20behind%20her.%20One%20heard%20the%20heartrending%20cry%20that%20came%20out%20of%20Yumna%20at%20that%20time%20as%20well%20as%20her%20shock%20as%20she%20became%20breathless%20seeing%20the%20horrific%20scene.%20This%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20frightening%20journalist%20pictures%20that%20came%20out%20during%20this%20war.%20Yumna%20is%20a%20journalist%20who%20appeared%20to%20be%20in%20her%20early%20thirties.%20But%20look%20at%20her%20now%2C%20more%20than%20a%20month%20into%20the%20war.%20She%20looks%20like%20a%2050%20or%2060-year-old%20woman.%20Yumna%E2%80%99s%20face%20bears%20the%20scars%20of%20reporting%20from%20the%20hellhole%20of%20human%20tragedy%2C%20living%20in%20a%20sort%20of%20hell%20herself%2C%20fleeing%20northern%20Gaza%20to%20the%20south%2C%20and%20filming%20herself%20comforting%20her%20own%20children%20as%20fire%20bombs%20rained%20down%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFour%20children%20of%20Muhammad%20al-Aloul%2C%20a%20photographer%20of%20the%20Turkish%20news%20agency%20Anadolu%20were%20killed%20in%20an%20airstrike.%20Salman%20al-Bashir%2C%20a%20journalist%20on%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%E2%80%99s%20TV%20channel%2C%20was%20reporting%20live%20when%20the%20news%20of%20his%20colleague%20Muhammad%20Abu%20Hattab%E2%80%99s%20death%20came.%20Salman%20al-Bashir%20tearfully%20removed%20his%20press%20jacket%2C%20which%20is%20worn%20by%20journalists%2C%20saying%20that%20journalists%20are%20not%20at%20all%20protected%20on%20this%20battlefield.%20The%20whole%20world%20saw%20the%20presenter%20who%20was%20sitting%20and%20talking%20with%20him%20in%20the%20studio%20also%20breaking%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmidst%20all%20this%2C%20Israel%20has%20informed%20the%20international%20media%20that%20it%20cannot%20guarantee%20the%20safety%20of%20journalists%20working%20in%20Gaza.%20Many%20journalists%E2%80%99%20family%20members%20were%20killed%20in%20Israeli%20bombings.%20Before%20the%20war%20started%2C%20Motaz%20Azaizah%20was%20a%2024-year-old%20photojournalist%2C%20Instagram%20influencer%2C%20and%20chronicler%20of%20daily%20life%20in%20Gaza%20and%20Israeli%20oppression.%20After%20the%20war%20started%2C%20all%20his%20attention%20was%20towards%20reporting%20deaths%20and%20devastation%20in%20Gaza.%20Azaiza%20went%20through%20the%20tragedy%20of%20filming%20the%20death%20of%20his%2015%20family%20members%20who%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20bombing%20of%20the%20Deir%20al-Bala%20refugee%20camp%20in%20Gaza.%20Videos%20of%20Azaiza%20and%20another%20journalist%2C%20Hind%20Khoudary%2C%20are%20now%20rarely%20seen.%20Both%20of%20them%20confirmed%20in%20a%20video%20aired%20a%20few%20days%20ago%20that%20they%20are%20alive%2C%20but%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20find%20their%20estranged%20family%20members%2C%20according%20to%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20journalist%20was%20seen%20rushing%20to%20the%20hospital%20in%20a%20car%20with%20two%20seriously%20injured%20toddlers%20on%20his%20lap.%20He%20was%20shouting%20to%20the%20camera%20that%20he%20just%20grabbed%20two%20wounded%20kids%20from%20among%20the%20many%20injured%20in%20the%20bombing%20and%20was%20going%20to%20the%20hospital%20with%20them.%20The%20children%E2%80%99s%20faces%20were%20covered%20in%20blood.%20The%20three%20brothers%20and%20father%20of%20Turkish%20news%20agency%20Anadolu%E2%80%99s%20photographer%20Ali%20Jadallah%20were%20killed%20in%20an%20Israeli%20airstrike.%20Ali%20himself%20released%20a%20picture%20of%20him%20driving%20to%20bury%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20body%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F687639%2Fisrael-palestine-war-benjamin-netanyahu-captain-america-problem%2F%5C%22%3EIsrael-Palestine%20War%3A%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20Captain%20America%20problem%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20journalism%20classes%20around%20the%20world%20teach%20that%20objectivity%20is%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20a%20journalist%E2%80%99s%20profession.%20Journalists%20in%20Gaza%20are%20going%20through%20a%20situation%20where%20they%20themselves%20turn%20into%20victims%2C%20subject%20to%20extreme%20kinds%20of%20pain%20and%20human%20tragedy%2C%20enduring%20death%20and%20separation.%20The%20cumulative%20impact%20of%20all%20this%20is%20that%20they%20themselves%20become%20news%20stories%20and%20objective%20reality%20of%20the%20world%20thus%20making%20them%20subjects%20of%20headlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAl%20Jazeera%20Arabic%20Channel%E2%80%99s%20Gaza%20Bureau%20Chief%2C%20Wael%20Dahdo%2C%20lost%20his%20wife%2C%2015-year-old%20son%2C%207-year-old%20daughter%20and%20grandchild%20in%20the%20bombing.%20A%20colleague%2C%20Yumna%20El%20Said%2C%20who%20fled%20to%20southern%20Gaza%2C%20told%20Al%20Jazeera%20that%20Dahdo%20remained%20in%20Gaza%20saying%20%E2%80%9CI%20cannot%20leave%20the%20Gazans.%E2%80%9D%20These%20words%2C%20spoken%20by%20a%20veteran%20journalist%20like%20Dahdo%2C%20show%20how%20complicated%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza%20is.%20The%20question%20arises%20whether%20a%20journalist%20can%20leave%20the%20place%20where%20he%20is%20assigned%2C%20and%20flee.%20In%20all%20probability%2C%20the%20journalist%20must%20have%20wondered%20who%20would%20tell%20the%20world%20the%20life%20stories%20of%20people%20who%20resolutely%20decided%20to%20stay%20put%20in%20Gaza%2C%20if%20he%20chose%20the%20option%20of%20running%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDahdo%20returned%20to%20war%20reporting%20the%20very%20next%20day%20after%20his%20entire%20family%20was%20killed.%20One%20cannot%20but%20wonder%20why%20Al%20Jazeera%20reassigned%20him%20to%20reporting%20instead%20of%20leaving%20him%20to%20mourn%20alone.%20But%20the%20violence%20in%20Gaza%20continues.%20If%20not%20Dahdo%2C%20who%20will%20give%20the%20news%3F%20Perhaps%2C%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20tragedy%20of%20his%20people%2C%20Dahdo%20is%20not%20ready%20to%20weep%20until%20this%20war%20is%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20the%20multifaceted%20images%20of%20bravery%20and%20media%20commitment%20are%20presented%20to%20the%20world%2C%20there%20are%20some%20important%20questions%20in%20the%20debate%20about%20journalism%20emerging%20from%20the%20Gaza%20war.%20Many%20layers%20of%20wartime%20journalism%2C%20including%20some%20unsavoury%20facets%2C%20can%20be%20deduced%20in%20those%20discussions.%20Still%2C%20amidst%20all%20these%20layers%2C%20what%20stands%20out%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20journalists%20of%20Gaza%2C%20from%20the%20content%20creators%20who%20had%20to%20become%20journalists%20on%20the%20war%20front%2C%20are%20truly%20worth%20a%20big%20salute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMedia%20action%3A%20questions%20raised%20by%20the%20Hamas-Israel%20war%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20among%20the%20troubling%20questions%20is%20the%20one%20related%20to%20the%20coverage%20of%20happenings%20on%20October%207%2C%20the%20day%20of%20mass%20murder.%20There%20were%20some%20journalists%20with%20Hamas%20who%20went%20along%20with%20the%20forces%20into%20Israel%20that%20day%20.%20Hamas%20attacked%20and%20killed%20soldiers%20and%20civilians%20alike.%20These%20were%20journalists%20from%20Gaza.%20But%20they%20were%20also%20freelancers%20reporting%20to%20the%20international%20media.%20Especially%20four%20of%20them.%20The%20four%20provided%20coverage%20of%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20to%20international%20news%20organisations%20such%20as%20the%20New%20York%20Times%2C%20Reuters%2C%20CNN%20and%20the%20Associated%20Press.%20These%20media%20houses%20published%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20journalists%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20videos%20of%20Hamas%20violence.%20This%20was%20first%20pointed%20out%20by%20Honest%20Reporting%2C%20a%20pro-Israel%20organization%20whose%20stated%20aim%20is%20to%20expose%20anti-Semitism%20in%20the%20media.%20They%20brought%20this%20presence%20of%20embedded%20journalists%20along%20with%20Hamas%20to%20public%20attention%20through%20an%20article%20published%20on%20their%20website%2C%20%E2%80%9CBroken%20Borders%3A%20AP%20%26amp%3B%20Reuters%20Pictures%20of%20Hamas%20Atrocities%20Raise%20Ethical%20Questions%E2%80%99%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221170%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6.jpg%201170w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6-300x136.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6-1024x464.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686477%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20five-year-old%20boy%20drinks%20bottled%20water%20delivered%20by%20UNICEF%20in%20the%20Khan%20Younis%20camp%20in%20Gaza.%20Photo%3A%20UNICEF%2FEyad%20El%20Baba%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDid%20these%20journalists%20go%20along%20knowing%20that%20such%20widespread%20violence%20was%20going%20to%20happen%3F%20If%20so%2C%20did%20they%20inform%20the%20concerned%20authorities%20in%20the%20media%20outlets%20that%20employ%20them%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20Reuters%3F%20And%20if%20these%20international%20media%20organisations%20had%20known%20this%2C%20are%20they%20not%20complicit%20in%20such%20a%20massacre%3F%20Moreover%2C%20Honest%20Reporting%20released%20another%20photo.%20It%20was%20a%20picture%20of%20Yahya%20Sinwar%2C%20the%20head%20of%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza%2C%20kissing%20one%20of%20the%20four%20journalists%20on%20his%20cheek.%20This%20picture%20was%20of%20Hassan%20Eslaiya%2C%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20in%20Gaza%20who%20provided%20CNN%20with%20news%20and%20pictures%20of%20the%20violence.%20A%20video%20also%20surfaced%20of%20Hassan%20Eslaiya%20riding%20a%20motorcycle%20with%20a%20man%20sitting%20on%20the%20back%20with%20a%20grenade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJournalism%20turning%20complex%20and%20confusing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20this%20disclosure%20by%20Honest%20Reporting%2C%20the%20Israeli%20Minister%20of%20Information%20and%20Communications%20issued%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20four%20international%20media%20organisations%20involved%3A%20%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Reuters%2C%20CNN%20and%20the%20Associated%20Press.%20The%20letter%20addressed%20the%20questions%20raised%20above.%20The%20Israeli%20side%20has%20alleged%20that%20these%20freelance%20journalists%20identify%20with%20the%20cause%20and%20actions%20of%20Hamas%20who%20committed%20the%20violence.%20To%20prove%20this%2C%20the%20letter%20pointed%20out%20the%20particular%20style%20of%20reporting%20of%20one%20of%20the%20reporters%20when%20the%20incident%20took%20place.%20Subsequently%2C%20all%20the%20four%20media%20houses%20issued%20a%20statement%20saying%20that%20they%20were%20not%20aware%20of%20the%20scale%20and%20nature%20of%20the%20violence.%20Reuters%20explained%20that%20on%20October%207%2C%20the%20day%20of%20the%20attack%2C%20they%20only%20bought%20photos%20from%20two%20Gazan%20freelance%20journalists%20who%20were%20on%20the%20Gaza-Israel%20border%2C%20and%20with%20whom%20they%20had%20no%20previous%20relationship.%20Moreover%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20time%20these%20photos%20were%20taken%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20they%20were%20taken%2045%20minutes%20after%20Israel%20officially%20announced%20the%20arrival%20of%20the%20attackers%2C%20Reuters%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Associated%20Press%20and%20CNN%20described%20the%20incident%20as%20simply%20gathering%20information%20from%20available%20sources%2C%20such%20as%20freelancers%2C%20as%20is%20often%20done%20in%20a%20sudden%20incident.%20And%20they%20said%20they%20had%20severed%20all%20ties%20with%20Hassan%20Eslaiya%2C%20the%20freelance%20journalist%20in%20Gaza.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%20%E2%80%93%20There%20is%20no%20evidence%20to%20make%20an%20allegation%20about%20our%20Gaza%20freelancer.%20This%20allegation%20is%20false%20and%20objectionable.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20accusation%20that%20could%20unnecessarily%20endanger%20journalists%20in%20Israel%20and%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20politics%20of%20media%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20summary%20of%20the%20problem%20discussed%20above%20has%20to%20factor%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20Hamas%20is%20both%20a%20political%20movement%20and%20an%20armed%20militant%20group%20that%20has%20openly%20adopted%20terrorist%20attacks%20as%20its%20modus%20operandi.%20This%20complexity%20makes%20media%20coverage%20of%20Hamas%20extremely%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20question%20is%20how%20%E2%80%98neutral%E2%80%99%20media%20work%20can%20be%2C%20emerging%20from%20a%20people%20who%20have%20been%20occupied%20and%20oppressed%20by%20Israel%20for%20many%20decades.%20The%20second%20aspect%20is%20that%20in%20the%20age%20of%20social%20media%2C%20where%20everyone%20is%20a%20citizen%20journalist%20and%20content%20creator%2C%20the%20boundaries%20between%20who%20is%20an%20ordinary%20citizen%20and%20who%20is%20a%20journalist%20are%20disappearing.%20The%20third%20question%20is%20this%20%E2%80%93%20a%20journalist%20gets%20information%20that%20such%20an%20act%20of%20violence%20is%20going%20to%20take%20place.%20Still%2C%20in%20all%20probability%2C%20those%20journalists%20were%20not%20fully%20aware%20of%20the%20horrific%20nature%20of%20the%20forthcoming%20violence.%20In%20such%20cases%2C%20journalists%20only%20get%20rumours%20first%20that%20something%20is%20going%20to%20happen.%20It%20is%20the%20natural%20instinct%20of%20the%20reporter%20to%20go%20after%20these%20bits%20and%20pieces%20of%20information%20or%20rumours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F686449%2Fpalestine-tiktok-territory-rights%2F%5C%22%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20More%20Than%20Just%20TikTok%3A%20How%20the%20Talk%20on%20Palestine%20Shifted%20from%20Territory%20to%20Rights%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20when%20the%20true%20nature%20of%20the%20violence%20is%20understood%20at%20some%20point%2C%20what%20steps%20can%20those%20journalists%20take%3F%20Is%20the%20primary%20mission%20to%20report%20the%20news%2C%20or%20to%20inform%20those%20concerned%2C%20to%20prevent%20violence%3F%20While%20reading%20history%2C%20we%20have%20seen%20instances%20of%20reporting%20where%20the%20stakeholders%20are%20informed%20by%20journalists%20in%20similar%20circumstances%20and%20the%20news%20is%20also%20reported.%20Sometimes%20we%20have%20also%20seen%20situations%20where%20both%20of%20these%20cannot%20be%20done.%20Moreover%2C%20reporting%20an%20event%20has%20extreme%20importance.%20If%20the%20violence%20is%20documented%2C%20it%20may%20even%20help%20identify%20the%20perpetrator%20later.%20Capturing%20what%20happened%20is%20important%20at%20several%20levels.%20Whether%20it%20is%20in%20Israel%20or%20Gaza%2C%20what%20involves%20journalists%20risking%20their%20lives%20to%20report%20a%20mass%20murder%20is%20also%20about%20justice%20for%20those%20dead%20people.%20If%20it%20is%20to%20be%20proven%20in%20later%20investigations%20what%20crimes%20have%20been%20committed%2C%20if%20both%20sides%20want%20justice%2C%20there%20needs%20to%20be%20rock%20solid%20evidence%2C%20and%20that%20is%20where%20the%20documentation%20as%20carried%20out%20by%20journalists%20becomes%20extremely%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEfforts%20to%20fact%20check%20and%20challenges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problems%20faced%20by%20international%20media%20reporting%20the%20war%20from%20outside%20without%20being%20able%20to%20go%20inside%20Gaza%20are%20many.%20Relying%20on%20freelancers%20in%20Gaza%20or%20the%20official%20Israeli%20military%20for%20news%20poses%20major%20challenges%20to%20factual%20reporting.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20while%20freelancers%E2%80%99%20reports%20from%20Gaza%20are%20invaluable%20documentation%2C%20they%20come%20with%20no%20other%20means%20of%20verifying%20the%20accuracy%20of%20the%20information%20they%20provide.%20The%20same%20problem%20exists%20with%20the%20information%20provided%20by%20the%20Israeli%20forces.%20Many%20content%20creators%20in%20Gaza%20have%20complained%20that%20their%20posts%20have%20been%20%E2%80%98shadow%20banned%E2%80%99%20by%20social%20media.%20There%20could%20be%20many%20factors%20behind%20such%20censorship%20by%20social%20media%20companies.%20These%20could%20include%20the%20need%20to%20censor%20picturisations%20of%20extreme%20violence%2C%20the%20depiction%20of%20close-ups%20of%20gruesome%20injuries%20and%20calls%20for%20violence.%20It%20can%20also%20be%20assumed%20that%20political%20messages%20against%20the%20politically%20mighty%20countries%20such%20as%20Israel%20and%20the%20United%20States%2C%20or%20messages%20that%20undermine%20the%20supremacy%20of%20the%20Western%20narrative%2C%20are%20also%20suppressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20media%20persons%2C%20content%20creators%2C%20and%20the%20ordinary%20people%20who%20are%20turned%20by%20war%20into%20conflict%20journalists%20believe%20they%20have%20a%20responsibility%20to%20speak%20the%20truth%20about%20Gaza%20to%20the%20world.%20Unfiltered%2C%20raw%20and%20authentic%20are%20the%20terminology%20by%20which%20the%20world%20generally%20describes%20the%20images%20and%20information%20provided%20by%20content%20creators%20in%20Gaza.%20The%20methods%20of%20fact-checking%20and%20scrutiny%20of%20potential%20errors%20at%20many%20editorial%20levels%20that%20are%20done%20in%20normal%2C%20curated%20journalism%20are%20well-nigh%20impossible%20in%20this%20war.%20Ghastly%20spectacles%20of%20horrific%20mass%20killings%20reach%20the%20audience%20uncut%20and%20unfiltered.%20The%20brutal%20honesty%20of%20these%20images%20is%20hard-hitting.%20Recognizing%20its%20implications%20to%20approved%20journalism%20practices%2C%20the%20mainstream%20media%20generally%20follow%20the%20pattern%20of%20masking%20the%20most%20horrific%20and%20tragic%20scenes%2C%20even%20in%20this%20war.%20But%20on%20social%20media%2C%20those%20scenes%20often%20come%20out%20without%20such%20precautions.%20The%20formal%20and%20informal%20consensus%20in%20journalism%20is%20that%20badly%20injured%20and%20mutilated%20corpses%20must%20not%20be%20shown%20as%20it%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20sanctity%20and%20dignity%20of%20human%20life.%20When%20there%20is%20a%20relentless%20massacre%20that%20continuously%20diminishes%20the%20value%20of%20human%20life%2C%20to%20argue%20for%20such%20restraint%20also%20becomes%20ridiculous%20and%20meaningless.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F12125115%2Fimage1170x530cropped-4.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221170%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F12125115%2Fimage1170x530cropped-4.jpg%201170w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F12125115%2Fimage1170x530cropped-4-300x136.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F12125115%2Fimage1170x530cropped-4-1024x464.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684525%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAl%20Shifa%20hospital%20is%20being%20used%20as%20shelter%20for%20displaced%20families%20in%20Gaza.%20Photo%3A%20WHO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20Gaza%20come%20out%20on%20pop%20in%20the%20media%20war%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEveryone%20now%20realises%20that%20there%20is%20a%20deadly%20war%20going%20on%20in%20Gaza%20as%20well%20as%20a%20media%20war.%20No%20one%20thinks%20that%20Gaza%20will%20fight%20and%20win%20a%20war%20waged%20against%20Israel%2C%20a%20deadly%20armed%20power%2C%20backed%20by%20an%20even%20greater%20force%2C%20the%20United%20States.%20But%20Gaza%20is%20far%20ahead%20in%20the%20media%20war.%20For%20that%2C%20we%20have%20to%20thank%20the%20aforementioned%20journalists%2C%20content%20creators%2C%20and%20ordinary%20people%20who%20have%20become%20war%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlmost%2025%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20this%20writer%20was%20working%20at%20the%20international%20desk%20of%20Asianet%20News%2C%20a%20Malayalam%20regional%20language%20channel%2C%20and%20preparing%20content%20for%20bulletins%2C%20then%20too%20the%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%20was%20a%20major%20and%20live%20topic.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20the%20Palestinians%20were%20mostly%20an%20unarmed%20population%20that%20picked%20up%20stones%20and%20threw%20them%20at%20Israeli%20forces.%20It%20was%20visibly%20so%20in%20the%20footage%20that%20was%20coming%20from%20there.%20And%20their%20voices%20were%20not%20legible%20at%20all.%20When%20they%20spoke%2C%20it%20was%20in%20Arabic%2C%20in%20a%20language%20unknown%20to%20the%20outside%20world%2C%20especially%20the%20western%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20say%20that%20social%20media%20has%20fostered%20a%20new%20breed%20of%20journalists%20in%20Gaza%2C%20there%20is%20another%20important%20thing%20that%20we%20need%20to%20understand%20and%20assimilate.%20Today%20those%20popular%20journalists%2Fcontent%20creators%20all%20speak%20good%20English%20to%20the%20world.%20The%20schools%20started%20in%20Gaza%20by%20UNRWA%20(United%20Nations%20Relief%20and%20Works%20Agency%20for%20Palestine%20Refugees%20in%20the%20Near%20East)%20and%20the%20education%20provided%20there%2C%20including%20English%2C%20have%20created%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20educated%20people%20in%20Gaza.%20This%20is%20also%20why%20Israel%20can%20be%20defeated%20in%20the%20media%20war%20even%20when%20Gaza%20is%20losing%20the%20war%20of%20arms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F684798%2Funited-states-israel-palestine%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20US%20Is%20Part%20of%20the%20Problem%20in%20Israel-Palestine%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20even%20accused%20UNRWA%20schools%20in%20Palestine%20run%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20as%20centres%20providing%20terrorist%20training.%20These%20allegations%20have%20been%20dismissed%20by%20the%20world%2C%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20with%20the%20contempt%20they%20deserve.%20But%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20UNRWA%20schools%20have%20played%20a%20role%20in%20empowering%20Gazans%2C%20especially%20the%20girls%20and%20women%20of%20Gaza.%20They%20got%20a%20new%20language%20to%20express%20their%20views%20to%20the%20world.%20They%20gained%20the%20confidence%20to%20do%20so%20through%20education.%20Interviews%20of%20many%20Gazans%20living%20outside%20Gaza%20%E2%80%93%20most%20of%20them%20professionals%2C%20academics%2C%20etc.%20%E2%80%93%20have%20already%20appeared%20on%20several%20TV%20channels.%20They%20articulate%20the%20politics%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20resistance%20to%20the%20world%20in%20English%2C%20with%20great%20erudition%20and%20ease.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20lesson%20for%20all%20oppressed%20people%20in%20the%20world%20who%20are%20looking%20for%20a%20path%20of%20resistance.%20It%20proves%20that%20an%20armed%20struggle%20is%20only%20a%20temporary%20solution.%20The%20power%20of%20knowledge%20will%20win%20the%20long%20battle%2C%20howsoever%20slow%20it%20is.%20The%20experience%20of%20journalists%20and%20content%20creators%20in%20Gaza%20continues%20to%20underscore%20that%20the%20English%20language%20is%20the%20best%20weapon%20to%20break%20the%20monopoly%20in%20the%20information%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheaidem.com%2Fen-how-conflict-in-gaza-changed-the-nature-of-journalism-and-reporting%2F%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheaidem.com%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20AIDEM%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701780327000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F19092706%2FF8t8SUEWMAAvoa0.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhow-the-war-in-palestine-is-being-broadcasted-amid-israels-growing-attacks-on-journalists%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Without%20the%20social%20media%20content%20creators-turned%20war%20reporters%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20world%20would%20never%20have%20understood%20the%20horrors%20of%20this%20war.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhow-the-war-in-palestine-is-being-broadcasted-amid-israels-growing-attacks-on-journalists%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Art%20World%20Is%20Succumbing%20to%20the%20Pressure%20of%20Ostracising%20Those%20Who%20Support%20Palestine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F30153449%2FACF098D3-6123-4B67-A2E4-DCA712B4.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20Jewish%20girl%20growing%20up%20in%20provincial%20England%20then%20Italy%2C%20%C2%A0I%20grew%20accustomed%20to%20anti-Semitism.%20%E2%80%9CDon%E2%80%99t%20be%20Jewey!%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20playground%20when%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20share%20sweets.%20%E2%80%9CSteen%3F%20Don%E2%80%99t%20you%20mean%20Stein%3F%E2%80%9D%20when%20I%20told%20teachers%20my%20mother%E2%80%99s%20maiden%20name.%20And%20over%20and%20over%3A%20%E2%80%9CYou%20don%E2%80%99t%20look%20Jewish%E2%80%9D%20though%20my%20blonde%2C%20snub-nosed%20looks%20make%20me%20a%20ringer%20for%20my%20Polish%20grandmother.%20One%20elderly%20Italian%20lady%20told%20me%20that%20she%20thought%20Jews%20struggled%20with%20Nazis%20because%20they%20were%20similar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20occasions%20are%20upsetting%20but%20I%20have%20never%20felt%20unsafe.%20This%20is%20not%20the%20experience%20of%20many%20Jews.%20If%20you%20attend%20synagogue%20and%20if%20your%20appearance%20marks%20you%20as%20Jewish%2C%20such%20badges%20of%20belonging%20make%20you%20a%20target.%20Since%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20attack%20of%20October%207%2C%20and%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20retaliation%2C%20reports%20of%20anti-Semitic%20attacks%20have%20soared%20in%20Europe%20and%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Islamophobia%20is%20also%20ever-present.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2021%2F03%2F1086452%5C%22%3E2021%20report%20by%20the%20UN%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20it%20is%20rising%20worldwide.%20The%20victory%20of%20anti-Islamic%20politician%20Geert%20Wilders%20in%20the%20Dutch%20elections%20mirrors%20the%20success%20of%20populist%20leaders%20such%20as%20Trump%20and%20Narendra%20Modi.%20Since%20October%207%2C%20that%20hatred%20has%20intensified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-right-wing-is-on-the-rise-globally%5C%22%3EThe%20Right%20Wing%20Is%20on%20the%20Rise%20Globally%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEquality%20and%20justice%20are%20collective%20operations.%20It%20is%20unjust%20to%20Muslims%20when%20governments%20and%20institutions%20fail%20to%20tackle%20Islamophobia%20with%20the%20same%20ferocity%20with%20which%20they%20tackle%20anti-Semitism.%20But%20it%20also%20endangers%20Jews%20because%20it%20suggests%20they%20deserve%20special%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conflation%20of%20anti-Zionism%20with%20anti-Semitism%20is%20also%20dangerous.%20There%20is%20an%20irrationality%20coiled%20within%20a%20concept%20that%20states%20Israel%20and%20Jewishness%20are%20the%20same%20thing.%20There%20is%20an%20old%20Jewish%20joke%20about%20one%20Jew%20needing%20two%20synagogues%3A%20the%20one%20he%20goes%20to%20and%20the%20one%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t.%20There%20are%20a%20myriad%20ways%20of%20being%20Jewish.%20Many%20of%20us%20identify%20as%20Jewish%20but%20also%20as%20a%20cornucopia%20of%20other%20things.%20To%20riff%20on%20the%20US%20poet%20Walt%20Whitman%2C%20Jews%20%E2%80%93%20like%20everyone%20else%20%E2%80%93%20contain%20multitudes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20culture%20sector%20is%20cracking%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20this%20unreason.%20Recently%20international%20dealer%20Lisson%20Gallery%20cancelled%20a%20show%20by%20Ai%20Weiwei%20after%20a%20tweet%20which%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theartnewspaper.com%2F2023%2F11%2F14%2Flisson-gallery-pulls-ai-weiwei-london-show-over-israel-hamas-war-tweet%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.theartnewspaper.com%2F2023%2F11%2F14%2Flisson-gallery-pulls-ai-weiwei-london-show-over-israel-hamas-war-tweet%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1701767731362000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2G3OuOrLPwOokhcBsemPF4%5C%22%3Ereportedly%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0stated%3A%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9CFinancially%2C%20culturally%2C%20and%20in%20terms%20of%20media%20influence%2C%20the%20Jewish%20community%20has%20had%20a%20significant%20presence%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20The%20annual%20%243%20billion%20aid%20package%20to%20Israel%20has%2C%20for%20decades%2C%20been%20touted%20as%20one%20of%20the%20most%20valuable%20investments%20the%20United%20States%20has%20ever%20made.%20This%20partnership%20is%20often%20described%20as%20one%20of%20shared%20destiny%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAi%20seemed%20to%20conflate%20Jewishness%20with%20Zionism.%20Furthermore%2C%20by%20implying%20that%20the%20Jewish%20community%20is%20a%20powerful%2C%20homogenous%20entity%2C%20he%20risked%20falling%20into%20anti-Semitic%20tropes%20that%20the%20Jews%20run%20Hollywood%20and%20Congress%20and%20are%20plotting%20world%20domination.%20Certainly%2C%20there%20are%20powerful%20Jews%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20There%20are%20many%20powerless%20ones%20too.%20Some%20support%20Israel.%20Many%20don%E2%80%99t.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Ai%20deleted%20his%20tweet.%20Given%20that%2C%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20Lisson%20have%20gone%20ahead%3F%20One%20erased%20tweet%2C%20from%20an%20artist%20indubitably%20committed%20to%20justice%2C%20does%20not%20make%20a%20pogrom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20parallels%20to%20be%20drawn%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F07%2F16%2Farts%2Fdesign%2Fdocumenta-resignation.html%5C%22%3Elast%20year%E2%80%99s%20debacle%20at%20the%20German%20contemporary%20arts%20festival%20Documenta%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20became%20embroiled%20in%20accusations%20of%20anti-Semitism%20stoked%20by%20a%20government%20which%20fails%20to%20distinguish%20between%20Zionism%20and%20Judaism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20baffling%20decisions%20have%20followed.%20For%20Documenta%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.artnews.com%2Fart-news%2Fnews%2Fdocumenta-denounces-selection-committee-member-bds-letter-israel-palestine-1234686372%2F%5C%22%3Eaccuse%20committee%20member%20Ranjit%20Hoskot%C3%A9%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20most%20sensitive%20of%20thinkers%2C%20of%20anti-Semitism%20is%20to%20drive%20out%20exactly%20the%20kind%20of%20reflective%2C%20nuanced%20voice%20that%20culture%20needs.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theartnewspaper.com%2F2023%2F11%2F22%2Fgerman-photo-biennial-cancelled-after-curators-posts-are-deemed-antisemitic%23%5C%22%3EA%20photography%20biennale%20actually%20cancelled%20itself%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20permit%20curation%20by%20photojournalist%2C%20teacher%20and%20activist%20Shahidul%20Alam%20whom%20they%20dubbed%20anti-Semitic%20for%20describing%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza%20as%20a%20genocide%20and%20comparing%20it%20to%20the%20Holocaust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fwhat-explains-the-political-rights-ascendancy-to-global-power%5C%22%3EWhat%20Explains%20the%20Political%20Right%E2%80%99s%20Ascendancy%20to%20Global%20Power%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20someone%20who%20knows%20Alam%20well%2C%20I%20can%20verify%20that%20he%20is%20not%20anti-Semitic.%20His%20courage%2C%20wisdom%20and%20humanity%20have%20been%20proven%20time%20and%20again%20not%20least%20when%20he%20went%20to%20prison%20for%20criticising%20his%20own%20government%20in%20Bangladesh.%20If%20I%20were%20in%20danger%20from%20anti-Semitism%20%E2%80%93%20or%20anything%20else%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20Alam%20I%20would%20want%20at%20my%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlam%20and%20I%20may%20debate%20his%20posts.%20I%20try%20to%20avoid%20comparisons%20between%20different%20atrocities%20because%20I%20believe%20that%20specificity%20is%20intrinsic%20to%20solutions.%20He%20and%20I%20will%20probably%2C%20as%20we%20have%20before%2C%20agree%20to%20differ.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArt%20should%20be%20a%20space%20where%20differences%20are%20permitted%20freedom.%20Art%20springs%20from%20friction.%20From%20contradiction%2C%20paradox%2C%20opposing%20forces%20birthing%20newness.%20Within%20that%20alchemy%2C%20more%20complex%2C%20imaginative%20truths%20emerge.%20For%20Alam%20and%20his%20team%2C%20the%20cancellation%20signals%20that%20voices%20from%20the%20Global%20South%20%E2%80%93%20the%20majority%20world%2C%20as%20Alam%20puts%20it%20%E2%80%93%20are%20not%20truly%20welcome%20beyond%20the%20region%20despite%20the%20lip%20service%20paid%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdiversity%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20repressions%20are%20in%20lockstep%20with%20a%20wider%20crackdown%20on%20expression.%20In%20the%20UK%2C%20Bristol%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-england-bristol-67496228%5C%22%3EArnolfini%20Gallery%20has%20dropped%20Palestinian%20events%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20fear%20they%20contradict%20state%20guidance%20that%20culture%20venues%20must%20remain%20apolitical%20or%20risk%20funding%20cuts.%20Given%20the%20political%20kernel%20of%20so%20much%20contemporary%20culture%2C%20this%20demand%20is%20absurd%20but%20it%20is%20indicative%20of%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20intolerant%20Tory%20administration.%20In%20truth%2C%20Arnolfini%20has%20held%20many%20political%20events%20so%20why%20do%20the%20Palestinian%20ones%20provoke%20censorship%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20is%20becoming%20Orwellian%20in%20its%20mechanisms%20of%20exclusion%2C%20erasure%20and%20silence.%20Even%20Jewish%20artists%2C%20such%20as%20Candice%20Breitz%2C%20are%20now%20being%20ostracised%20for%20their%20Palestinian%20sympathies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20anti-Semitism%20and%20there%20is%20Islamophobia%3A%20real%2C%20violent%20ideologies%20that%20destroy%20lives.%20There%20are%20also%20a%20million%20ghosts%2C%20fantasies%2C%20mis-speakings%20and%20mis-perceptions%20of%20those%20hate%20crimes.%20We%20need%20to%20be%20able%20to%20distinguish%20them.%20We%20need%20to%20understand%20who%20has%20the%20power%20to%20kill%20us%20and%20who%20is%20expressing%20an%20opinion%20with%20which%20we%20may%20not%20agree%20but%20which%20does%20not%20endanger%20us.%20Otherwise%2C%20we%20will%20waste%20our%20energy%20fighting%20shadows%20while%20the%20real%20monsters%20thrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20argued%20that%20Ai%E2%80%99s%20tweet%20could%20be%20construed%20as%20anti-Semitic%2C%20my%20non-Jewish%20partner%20didn%E2%80%99t%20get%20it.%20I%20explained.%20He%20got%20it.%20Or%20said%20he%20did.%20That%E2%80%99s%20ok.%20That%E2%80%99s%20two%20people%20having%20different%20histories.%20(My%20partner%E2%80%99s%20Argentinian%20and%20objects%20every%20time%20I%20forget%20to%20describe%20those%20islands%20in%20the%20South%20Atlantic%20as%20Las%20Malvinas.)%20That%E2%80%99s%20all%20of%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20horror%20in%20Gaza%20is%20ripping%20faultlines%20through%20the%20art%20sector.%20The%20failure%20of%20major%20institutions%20to%20condemn%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20war%20crimes%20in%20Gaza%20as%20they%20condemned%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20has%20triggered%20outrage%2C%20protests%20and%20sit-ins.%20Those%20who%20disagree%20say%20that%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20massacre%20makes%20such%20comparisons%20shaky.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETime%20and%20again%20I%20remember%20lines%20by%20the%20radical%20poet%20Adrienne%20Rich%2C%20who%20was%20Jewish%20on%20her%20father%E2%80%99s%20side.%20%E2%80%9CSplit%20at%20the%20root%2FNeither%20Gentile%20nor%20Jew%20%5B%E2%80%A6but%5D%20I%E2%80%99m%20a%20good%20reader%20of%20histories.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20be%20superlative%20historians%20to%20recognise%2C%20as%20Ant%C3%B3nio%20Guterres%20said%2C%20that%20October%207%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.france24.com%2Fen%2Fvideo%2F20231024-hamas-attacks-did-not-happen-in-a-vacuum-guterres-says%5C%22%3Edidn%E2%80%99t%20happen%20in%20a%20vacuum%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Nor%20did%20the%20atrocities%20in%20Gaza.%20The%20ghosts%20of%20millions%20in%20Europe%20and%20Palestine%20haunt%20those%20dying%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20I%20condemn%20October%207%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20believe%20Palestinian%20people%20should%20pay%20for%20Hitler%E2%80%99s%20crimes.%20Art%20stakes%20itself%20on%20empathy%3A%20between%20artist%20and%20subject%3B%20art%20and%20viewer.%20It%20also%20wagers%20on%20mystery%3A%20that%20which%20bewilders%20us%2C%20makes%20us%20hesitate.%20Sometimes%20it%20makes%20us%20angry.%20Sometimes%20it%20redeems%20us.%20Sometimes%20it%20does%20both.%20It%E2%80%99s%20somewhere%20to%20backtrack%2C%20rethink%20then%20recomplicate.%20The%20lady%20who%20compared%20the%20Jews%20to%20Nazis%20had%2C%20as%20a%20young%20woman%2C%20hidden%20a%20Jew%20in%20her%20attic%20during%20the%20war%20at%20enormous%20personal%20risk.%20Humanity%20is%20as%20multi-faceted%20as%20a%20diamond.%20Art%20is%20a%20place%20where%20its%20strangeness%20can%20shine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cancellations%20damage%20the%20freedom%20and%20creativity%20they%20claim%20to%20protect.%20As%20James%20Baldwin%20put%20it%3A%20%E2%80%9CLife%20is%20more%20important%20than%20art.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20art%20is%20so%20important.%E2%80%9D%20If%20dialogue%20across%20difference%20is%20shut%20down%20in%20the%20house%20of%20culture%2C%20what%20hope%20remains%20elsewhere%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERachel%20Spence%20is%20a%20poet%20and%20arts%20writer.%20Her%20latest%20book%20is%20%3C%2Fem%3EVenice%20Unclocked%3Cem%3E%20(2022%2C%20Ivory%20Press).%20Her%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3EFinancial%20Times%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3EHyperallergic%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Art%20Newspaper%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701778558000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F30153449%2FACF098D3-6123-4B67-A2E4-DCA712B4.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fart-world-succumbing-pressure-ostracising-support-palestine%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20conflation%20o